description:
Responsibilities:

Perform routine on line and finished food products inspection at various stages on the production line to implement ISO/HACCP policy.
Assist in implementing and maintain the documentation system and quality management system.
Support the implementation of food safety, hygiene and quality assurance operation policies, guidelines and procedures to ensure the entire production process is in compliance with the corporate standard.
Coordinate and participate work safety, quality assurance and hygiene procedures training to related staff.
Assist in other ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Diploma holder or above in biochemistry, Food Science or related disciplines;
Self-motivated, independent and with good communication skill;
Well-organized with good analytical skill;
Proficient in PC applications including Chinese word processing;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese / Cantonese;
Working location: Tai Po Industrial Estate (with shuttle bus)
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

Interested parties please apply with full resume, state current and expected salaries via clicking "Apply Now".


All applications and data collected will be treated in strict confidence and used exclusively for recruitment purposes.  Only short listed candidates will be invited for interview.  The company will retain the applications for a maximum period of 6 months and may refer suitable candidates to other vacancies within the Group.

Responsibilities:
Implementation and maintenance of quality management system;
Perform food safety, hygiene inspection and monitor in production floor to ensure the operation complies with all statutory requirements and in-house hygiene standard;
Focus on quality enhancement;
Assist in ad hoc projects as assigned.
 Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in Food & Nutritional Science or equivalent;
5 years relevant experience in food manufacturing industry;
Knowledge of GMP/ HACCP & ISO 9001 and food regulation would be an advantage;
Independent, responsible with good communication skill;
Proficient in Chinese Word, Excel and PowerPoint;
Candidate with more experience could be considered as Assistant QA Manager
Interested parties, please forward your resume stating salary expectation and available date to us.

For more information of Saint Honore Cake Shop, please visit www.cr-asia.com
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Personal data provided will be used for recruitment purpose only. The information collected might also be disclosed to other associated companies of the Fung Group for job matching of similar vacancies.
The provision of full and complete information in support of your application is necessary for selection purposes. Applicant has the right to request access to and correction of personal data collected from him/her in writing to the Human Resource Manager by post to P.O. Box 92408, Tsim Sha Tsui Post Office, Hong Kong.

A Manager, Technical Services is now required as a result of business growth:

Responsibilities:
• Responsible for the product development of our health products (Adrien Gagnon) for Hong Kong, the Mainland & Asian markets;
• Coordinate with the R&D team to develop product formulation/ modification and prepare documentation in order to cope with related registration requirements;
• Provide technical advice and work closely with the commercial team on marketing / promotional materials and nutrition labels, etc.;
• Develop regulatory strategy and communicate the regulatory trend and its business impact to management and cross-functional teammates;
• Manage product registration and present registration dossiers to expedite the approval progress;
• Monitor the quality of raw materials/ finished products / facilities to ensure the full compliance of audits and inspections by HK FEHC and CFS;
• Provide professional assessment and analysis to our customer service team to settle customer’s complaint;
• Organize health talk to corporate associations and deliver new product & compliance training to the retailers, promoters and cross-functional teammates.

Requirements:
• A Master’s / Bachelor’s degree in Food & Nutritional Science, Pharmacy or other related discipline;
• A minimum of 8 years’ experience in R&D (health supplement and / or food), regulatory affairs and quality assurance;
• Previous experience in Hong Kong, the Mainland & Asian markets is a plus;
• Solid knowledge in regulatory submissions, policy and procedures;
• Hands-on experience in GMP and ISO is an advantage;
• Demonstrate advanced skills in report writing and documentation;
• Decisive, attentive to details and with strong organizational skills;
• Can work under pressure and a fast-paced working environment.

Thank you for your interest in a career with CK Life Sciences. Competitive compensation and benefits package will be offered to the right candidate. We operate a 5-day workweek, and our benefits cover retirement, health and life. Regular shuttle bus service is also provided with pick-ups and drop-offs at designated and convenient locations.

To apply for our position, you should write, enclosing a current resume to Chief Manager, Human Resources & Administration, CK Life Sciences Limited, 2 Dai Fu Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Hong Kong or by clicking the APPLY NOW button. For more company information, please visit www.ck-lifesciences.com.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially by authorized personnel for recruitment-related purposes within the Group.

Responsibilities

Support the implementation of “5-S” management system and perform on-site audit in restaurants;
Maintain environmental, health & safety record and documents;
Follow up work injury case and prepare related reports and documents;
Organize the occupational safety training and modify & update the training materials from time to time;
Ensure the operations in restaurants are in compliance with safety regulations and corporate requirements;
Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned

Requirements:

Diploma holder or above in related disciplines;
A minimum of 1 year’s working experience in clerical support, recent graduates will be also considered;
Experience in F&B operations and restaurant group is preferable;
Knowledge in Safety and Health Ordinance is an advantage;
Strong presentation and communications skills;
Good inter-personal skills & able to work independently;
Good written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint
Working Location : Fotan



We offer competitive package and benefits:

         Five-Day work week
         3 Days Marriage Leave
         5 Days Full Pay Paternity Leave
         Family-Friendly Leave
         Birthday Leave
         Free Duty Meal
         Staff Discount
         Medical Allowance
         Insurance Plan
         Promotion Opportunities

For more company information, please visit our web site at www.taihing.com

Interested parties please send full resume with expected salary and availability to the Human Resources Department via email.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only used for employment-related purposes. Applicants who are not invited for interview within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.

Working in Tao Heung Group, besides remuneration and benefits, you can also
1) Get a chance to work in one of the largest F&B groups,
2) Get cross-border exposure, and
3) Get some challenging yet fulfilling and rewarding experience.

Please join us as:

Laboratory Technician

Job Description:

Perform sampling and testing of raw materials and finished products;

Execute onsite sampling for food and environmental samples;
Analyze test data; verify results and prepare reports;
Conduct equipment calibration and maintenance;
Monitor factory environment and hygiene conditions.
Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Food Technology, Food Science, Chemistry, Biology or Biochemistry;
2 years' food manufacturing or laboratory experience in food analysis or quality control;
Good analytical and organizational skills;
Knowledge in food production and processing would be an advantage;
Fresh graduates are welcome.
Interested parties please apply with resume, current salary, expected salary and contact numbers to the Human Resources Manager, Tao Heung Group Ltd. by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Application letters collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

